/* Economic democracy */ Since Mill identified as a socialist in his autobiography, saying "In short, I was a democrat, but not the least of a Socialist. We were now much less democrats than I had been... but our ideal of ultimate improvement went far beyond Democracy, and would class us decidedly under the general designation of Socialists." I believe it is better language to specify Marxism as the type of socialism to which he objected. Being a socialist himself, socialism is the wrong word.
